## DMEDI Phase Deliverables

### Phase 1: Define

| Deliverable | Description | Format |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| Project Charter | Problem statement, business case, scope, team roles | 1-page template |
| MGPP | Goals, metrics, project plan, resources | Gantt chart + narrative |
| Risk Management Plan | Identified risks, mitigation strategies, FMEA | Risk matrix |

### Phase 2: Measure

| Deliverable | Description | Format |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| Voice of Customer | Customer needs, Kano analysis, affinity diagrams | VoC summary report |
| QFD | House of Quality with customer priorities | HoQ matrix |
| Statistical Analysis | Descriptive statistics, distributions, visualizations | Minitab/JMP/R output |
| Process Capability | Cp, Cpk, Pp, Ppk analysis | Capability study report |

### Phase 3: Explore

| Deliverable | Description | Format |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| Concept Selection | Pugh matrix, AHP scoring, decision criteria | Selection matrix |
| Hypothesis Testing | t-tests, ANOVA, chi-square with interpretation | Statistical report |
| Design FMEA | Failure modes, effects, causes, RPN prioritization | DFMEA worksheet |

### Phase 4: Develop

| Deliverable | Description | Format |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| Design of Experiments | Full-factorial, fractional factorial, or RSM | DOE report |
| Response Surface | Contour plots, optimization, confirmation runs | RSM report |
| Robust Design | Parameter design, tolerance analysis, S/N ratios | Robust design summary |

### Phase 5: Implement

| Deliverable | Description | Format |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| Prototype / Pilot | Test results, data analysis, lessons learned | Pilot report |
| Process Control Plan | Control charts, monitoring strategy, response plan | Control plan |
| Final Report | Executive summary, all phases, recommendations | Comprehensive report |

## Evaluation Criteria

| Criterion | Weight | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| Phase completeness | 25% | All 5 DMEDI phases completed with deliverables |
| Tool proficiency | 20% | Correct use of Minitab/JMP/R |
| Statistical rigor | 25% | Valid hypothesis tests, DOE, regression |
| Practical application | 20% | Actionable results |
| Presentation quality | 10% | Clear communication |
| **Total** | **100%** | |

